<section class="section" data-sec="method">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head"><div><span class="no">The apparatus</span><h2>Where do these numbers come from?</h2></div></div>
    <div class="prose prose--kb">
      {%- if feed.marketStats %}
      <p>Most market-stat pages are syndicated widgets. These aren&rsquo;t. Everlane runs its own
      data pipeline: listings flow from <strong>Stellar MLS</strong> (via MLS GRID) into our own
      database several times a day, and the statistics on this page are computed there by
      database queries &mdash; median sale price, days on market, active inventory, months of
      supply &mdash; then baked into this page as plain HTML with the computation timestamp shown.</p>
      {%- else %}
      <p>Most market-stat pages are syndicated widgets. This one won&rsquo;t be. Everlane is standing up
      its own data pipeline: once the MLS data feed is connected, listings will flow from
      <strong>Stellar MLS</strong> into our own database through the day, and the statistics on this page
      will be computed there by database queries &mdash; median sale price, days on market, active
      inventory, months of supply &mdash; then baked into this page as plain HTML with the computation
      time shown.</p>
      {%- endif %}
      <p>Three commitments, permanent:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No AI-generated numbers.</strong> An AI model never computes or estimates a
        statistic here. Models draft narrative (below) from the computed numbers; the numbers
        themselves are SQL over the feed, every time.</li>
        <li><strong>Real data or nothing.</strong> If the pipeline hasn&rsquo;t run, the band above
        shows no figures &mdash; you will never see a placeholder number dressed up as data.</li>
        <li><strong>Visible timestamps.</strong> Every stat surface names its computation time and
        the period it covers, per MLS display rules.</li>
      </ul>
      <p><a href="/ai/">See how this site runs &rarr;</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

